The paper deals with the classification of a new class of binary codes called complementary information set (CIS) codes, which have practical applications in cryptography. This makes cs.IT (Information Theory) the most likely sub-category, as it deals with the study of information processing, including coding theory. The paper also discusses the use of CIS codes in masking cryptographic algorithms against side channel attacks, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the classification of binary codes, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions the use of equivalence relations on matrices, which is a topic in cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
